name: &cHow to train your &c&lCHICKEN&c! &8- &7The Ducity Story
author: Matty
description: You have to train a chicken that wishes they could one day fly and get back to interacting with other chickens that left him because he was different than all the others!

LookDialog.&d&lLisa: Hey [PLAYER], do you want to learn how to train a chicken?
LookDialog.[PLAYER]: Of course I would, who wouldn't!?!?
LookDialog.&d&lLisa: Well, you came to the right place.
Come on inside for a short little story.
A long time ago your city was infested with chickens.

Dialog.&d&lLisa: Roaming the streets and frequently attacking residents and damaging property.
But, there was this one chicken not as powerful as the other chickens.
He was not as strong as the other chickens,
nor did he know how to fly.
All the others had made fun of him for being weak.

LookDialog.&d&lLisa: Since then, he's been trying to fly but can not succeed.
Are you ready to grow up, find your courage, and learn how to train a chicken?
But, first you must go to him.
I believe he is still down there behind my house!

Objective: Talk to Ducity behind Lisa's Home

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Oh, well hello there little chicken!
So I am guessing you can't fly like the others?
Oh! Wow you can talk?
How could I help you?
Dialog.&b&lDucity: I need help learning to fly, run, fight, screech, and problem solve.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Okay, so should we start with some training exercises?
Let's see your current ability to fly.
Oh wow... We've got some work to do.

Dialog.&b&lDucity: Yea, I haven't learned how to do anything as a chicken.
Before they left me here all alone they said that every feather I grow the higher I will fly...
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Really? I saw some feathers around here somewhere.
I can go find them and give them to you if you want.
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Sure, let's see if it works!

Objective: Find 10 Feathers and Give them to the Chicken!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: There you go.
Now, try and fly!

Dialog.&b&lDucity: I really need some practice flying.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: I have a great idea to help!
I will put an egg down and when I do you have to fly to it!
Great! Let me go ask &dLisa&r for some eggs!

Objective: Talk to Lisa about getting Eggs

Dialog.&d&lLisa: Oh hey, you're back so early?
Did you finish up the training that quick?
Dialog.[PLAYER]: No, I actually came to ask where I could find chicken eggs at.
I am going to use them to make the chicken practice flying!
Since chickens like to nest their eggs, they will have to fly to them.
Dialog.&d&lLisa: Oh, that sounds like a great idea.
I keep them out front, but be careful with them!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Will do, thanks!

Objective: Grab the Eggs from Lisa's front yard

Dialog.&6&lNyx: What were you thinking leaving this chicken all alone!
You should have known I was watching!
You're lucky! I am not feeling that evil today...
Fight me if you want the chicken!

Objective: Battle Nyx
SendMessage: &4&lWARNING> &7Leaving this area without having '&e/fly&7' requires you to use the Teleporter located at '&e/spawn&7'!

BattleNpc.[PLAYER]: I can and will defeat you to save &bDucity&r!
I told you I would defeat you!

BattleNpc.&6&lNyx: Looks like you'll have to try again later!

LookDialog.&6&lNyx: Well, I am glad that you think that!

Dialog.&6&lSpike: I don't think he is going anywhere...
Dialog.&6&lDraco: Yea... You thought you won after &6Nyx &rbut you have to beat us too!
Dialog.&6&lSpike: You know how I like my eggs, Terri-Fried!

Objective: Battle Spike

BattleNpc.&6&lSpike: No... You haven't seen the end of me!
I will get you for this!!!
Come back when you are stronger!

Dialog.&6&lDraco: But, not good enough to beat me!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Are you sure about that?!?
Dialog.&6&lDraco: Well umm... Yes, you are only level &e[LEVEL]&r!

Objective: Battle Draco

BattleNpc.[PLAYER]: You're going to be salty after I beat you!

BattleNpc.&6&lDraco: This is not the end of me...
Come back when you are stronger!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Did you just fall?
Dialog.&b&lDucity: No, I was checking if gravity still works...
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Likely story...
Yea! I think we could train you for flying here!
I have the eggs with me, and there are plenty of cliffs here.

Objective: Click the 1st Egg to Call Ducity over to it

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Here, let's start off with a simple one.

Objective: Click the 2nd Egg to Call Ducity over to it

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hmm. This one seems just a little bit harder
but, you should be able to do it!

Dialog.&b&lDucity: With these new feathers I can fly so much better!

Objective: Click the 3rd Egg to Call Ducity over to it

Dialog.[PLAYER]: This one is a bit higher off the ground.
Come and get it!

Dialog.&b&lDucity: Pokaawk! That was a hard one.

Objective: Click the 4th Egg to Call Ducity over to it

Dialog.[PLAYER]: This one you can jump from your current spot!

Objective: Click the 5th Egg to Call Ducity over to it

Dialog.[PLAYER]: This is the last one. You can do it!

Objective: Talk to Ducity

Dialog.&b&lDucity: Wow! I feel like I am a master at this!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great! Now it's time to teach you how to run.
There is no better way to learn how to run,
than doing it to get faster!
I got to say... It is getting late.
Would you like to race me to the &eOasis Farm &rbarn?

Objective: Race Ducity to the Oasis Farm Barn

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Wow! How did you beat me?
Dialog.&b&lDucity: I just ran as fast as I could to get here.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: That is awesome.
Seems you are already a pro in running!
Let's get right into training you for fighting.
I'll guide you through the battles.
I ordered the best himself to come fight us!
His name is &f&lCLOUD THE SAVAGE&r!
He absolutely hates chickens.
I dont know why though, who could possibly hate chickens?!?!?
Well anyway, he should be here any second now.
There he is!
Inside the barn.

Dialog.&f&lCloud: I am Cloud, I will help you prepare for fights.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great! I will fight Cloud as a demonstration.
This will help you prepare for battles.

Objective: Fight Cloud as a demonstration to Ducity

BattleNpc.&f&lCloud: Good job! Let's do one more battle
to make sure &bDucity &runderstands how to battle.
Well, that wasn't a very good demonstration...

Objective: Fight Cloud as a demonstration to Ducity

BattleNpc.&f&lCloud: Great work! I think that was a perfect demonstration!
Well, that wasn't a very good demonstration...

Dialog.&f&lCloud: Looks like he understands how to fight.
I'm going to head back home now.
I wish you and &bDucity&r the best in your training!
Even though I don't like chickens...
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Thanks again Cloud!
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Yes, thank you! I think I got the hang of it from watching you guys.

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great! Would you like to practice battling me?

Objective: Fight Ducity

BattleNpc.&b&lDucity: I don't have the best pokémon.
Well even though you won, I am pretty sure I got the hang of it.
Yay! I got the hang of it.
Keep battling me until you can defeat me!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great work! I say we head back to &eNoobville &ras it is getting late.
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Pokaawk! I will sleep at the Great Chicken statue.

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Okay, I will meet you there tomorrow morning

Objective: Sleep on the Couch

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Zzzzzz...

Objective: Meet Ducity at The Great Chicken statue!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Today we will be working on your screeching!
This will be very useful to help scare off predators.
Give me your best screech.
That wasn't that bad.
But, imagine that I am your enemy...
or if I was evil like &6Nyx &ryesterday!
Much better!
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Pokaawk! Look at the yellow shop!

Dialog.&6&lNyx: I told you I'd be back.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Quick &bDucity&r, attack!
Wow! You did great!
So... What's next?
Oh yes! I have the perfect idea for that!
My good friend named &6The Mad Hatter &rhas been asking for some help.

Objective: Talk to The Mad Hatter

Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Hey, [PLAYER]! Long time no see...
I've needed your help for a while!
I've been meaning to test your problem solving capabilities.
I am testing if people with hats can solve problems faster!
So I set up a little course for you, it is filled with riddles.
Each item that is the answer to the riddles can be found behind this area.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great! &bDucity&r and I will work on finding all the items of your wishes!
Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Sounds good!
The first riddle is: I start with T end with T and am filled with T!
Send me a call over your &cPokégear &rafter you find the first item!
I am going to go sell some hats.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: You got it!
So... What do you think it is?
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Ah, this is a tough one.
I feel like I heard this one before.
I think its some sort of pot.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Great thinking, let's look around.

Objective: Find the Item! - I start with T end with T and am filled with T
Call the Mad Hatter - /pokecall

Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Hello!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hey, I found the first item, it was a Tea Pot!
Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Great work!
The next riddle is:
From this pot, the adults can drink a lot.
Good luck!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Any ideas on this one?
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Nope, I am stumped on this one...

Objective: Find the Item! - From this pot, the adults can drink a lot.
Call the Mad Hatter - /pokecall

Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: You found the second one that fast?
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Yes, we did!
Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Great job!
The next riddle is a little more tricky.
It is: I have a face that doesn't frown,
I have hands that do not wave, I have no mouth,
just a familiar sound, I don't walk - but I move around?
Good luck!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Hmm... This seems a bit tricky.
Great thinking!

Objective: Find the Item! - I have a face that doesn’t frown, I have hands that do not wave, I have no mouth, just a familiar sound, I don't walk - but I move around?
Call the Mad Hatter - /pokecall

Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Great you found it?
If you could find that one these next two shouldn't be that hard.
Here is the next riddle:
Fluttering, flying and flitting so free, from flower to flower is where you'll find me?
Call me later!

Dialog.&b&lDucity: Hmm... This one is all on you.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Let's check around, maybe it's near the garden?

Objective: Find the Item! - Fluttering, flying and flitting so free, from flower to flower is where you'll find me?
Call the Mad Hatter - /pokecall

Dialog.[PLAYER]: We found the item for your fourth riddle!
Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Great work! I only have one more in store for you!
This one should be very simple.
Here it is, From my skin, a paper can be made,
but I prefer that you use me for some shade.
Good luck!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Let's try and find this without helping each other.
Where?

Objective: Find the Item! - From my skin, a paper can be made, but I prefer that you use me for some shade.
Call the Mad Hatter - /pokecall

Dialog.&6&lMad Hatter: Wow! You are really good at riddles!
Thanks for helping me test my theory.
I'm going to go back to selling hats now. See you later!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Bye!

LookDialog.[PLAYER]: You are officially ready to return home to all the other chickens!

Objective: Go to Lisa's House

LookDialog.&d&lLisa: I just finished making this statue.
I just thought it looked nice.
You know, I am sort of a chicken freak.
How did you like training a chicken?
LookDialog.[PLAYER]: It was fun, except we ran into a few hiccups...
But, we fixed them and took down some evil villains along the way!
LookDialog.&d&lLisa: Wow! Sounds fantastic! What all did &bDucity &rlearn?
LookDialog.[PLAYER]: I taught him how to fly, run, fight, screech, and solve problems!
Really?!?! We can show them how much you have learned, &bDucity&r!

Dialog.[PLAYER]: Oh, don't be. It will be fun!
Let's go!

Objective: Head on down to where you found Ducity

Dialog.&b&lDucity: You are the best trainer ever!
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Ahh, no problem.
Dialog.&b&lDucity: I could never have learned all these qualities if you weren't here.
Here, take some stuff as repayment.
Dialog.[PLAYER]: Wow! Thank you!
Dialog.&b&lDucity: Thanks again! Come and visit sometime!
